record_data.record_plain_text:
EAST KENTUCKY POWER COOPERATIVE, INC. SPECIFICATION OF REVENUE REQUIREMENT
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service (EKPC Transmission Zone - Cooper Generating Plant and Spurlock Generating Plant)
The East Kentucky Power Cooperative, Inc. ("EKPC") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") to the PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM") system from EKPC's Cooper Generating Plant (units 1 and 2) and from EKPC's Spurlock Generating Plant (units 1-4) (together, "Cooper Spurlock Units"). The Cooper-Spurlock Units are located within the EKPC transmission pricing zone of PJM. This Specification sets forth EKPC's revenue requirements for the provision of Reactive Supply Service to PJM from the Cooper-Spurlock Units, as contemplated by Schedule 2 of the PJM Open Access Transmission Tariff. EKPC's annual and monthly revenue requirements are set forth below. Total charges for any 12-month period will not be less than the product of 12 times the monthly revenue requirement specified below.
ANNUAL AND MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENTS: Cooper Generating Plant (units 1 and 2) Annual Revenue Requirement is $341,964.00 Spurlock Generating Plant (units 1-4) Annual Revenue Requirement is $1,956,167.00 Combined Annual Revenue Requirement is $2,298,131.00 Combined Monthly Revenue Requirement is $191,510.86
EFFECTIVE DATE: July 1, 2013 pursuant to the orders issued in FERC Docket No. EL13-68-000 on July 26, 2013 (144 FERC ? 61,066) and May 8, 2014 (147 FERC ? 61,097)
